{{italic title}} {{Expand French|Nature morte aux fruits (Gustave Courbet)|date=July 2018}} [[File:Gustave_Courbet_044.jpg|thumb|''Still Life with Apples'' (1872)]] '''''Still-Life with Fruits''''' (French - ''Nature morte aux fruits'') is a series of [[still life]] paintings produced between 1871 and 1872 by [[Gustave Courbet]], marking his return to painting after the silence forced on him by the [[Franco-Prussian War]], the [[Paris Commune]], imprisonment and illness.
